Reverse the Case of a String
Write a Java program to convert all uppercase letters in a string to lowercase and all lowercase letters to uppercase.
Sample Input
JaVa ProGRam
Sample Output
jAvA pROgrAM


Coding...:
import java.util.*;

public class Program {
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        Scanner a = new Scanner(System.in);
        
        while (a.hasNext()) {
            // 1. Read the word first so we can find its length and check its characters
            String word = a.next(); 
            
            // 2. Fixed 'strlen' to 'word.length()' to correctly loop through the string
            for (int i = 0; i < word.length(); i++) {
                // 3. Get the character at index 'i' instead of always index '0'
                char s = word.charAt(i); 
                
                if (s == '.') {
                    return; // Stops the program completely when a period is hit
                }
                
                // 4. Fixed the 'else if' branch to convert uppercase to lowercase
                if (Character.isLowerCase(s)) {
                    s = Character.toUpperCase(s);
                } else if (Character.isUpperCase(s)) {
                    s = Character.toLowerCase(s);
                }
                
                // 5. Changed 'println' to 'print' so characters stay grouped as a word
                System.out.print(s); 
            }
            // 6. Print a space after finishing the word
            System.out.print(" "); 
        }
    }
}
